Third-party code: VibeVoice
===========================

The Python modules in this directory (murmur/modeling/vibevoice/) are vendored
and adapted from the VibeVoice project by Microsoft, used under the MIT License.
The upstream copyright notice and license text are preserved in the LICENSE file
in this directory.

    Upstream: https://github.com/microsoft/VibeVoice
    License:  MIT (Copyright (c) 2025 Microsoft)

Modifications made for Murmur:
  - Only the ASR-related model, configuration, tokenizer, and processor modules
    are included — a subset of the upstream package (the streaming/TTS diffusion
    path is omitted).
  - Files were adapted to integrate with the Murmur inference engine and its
    KV-cache eviction policies.

These modifications are distributed under Murmur's MIT License (see the LICENSE
file at the repository root).
